Guatemala
 Examples have been found at many sites on the Pacific coast of Guatemala including Takalik Abaj, Monte Alto, Bilbao and El Ba&lt;U+00FA&gt;l. The earliest examples of potbellied monuments have been dated to the Middle Preclassic, with the majority dating to the Late Preclassic.22
Well-preserved examples of Late Preclassic potbelly sculptures have been found at Bilbao, on the coastal plain, and at Kaminaljuyu in the Guatemalan highlands.23 A small potbelly monument has been found at the major Maya city of Tikal in the lowlands of Pet&lt;U+00E9&gt;n in Guatemala.24
